12 "§1749.28. Dispute resolution for BEAD Program-funded projects
13 A. This Section applies solely to broadband construction projects funded
14 pursuant to the federal Broadband Equity, Access, and Deployment, or BEAD,
15 Program as administered by the office of broadband, development and
16 connectivity, which will be referred to in this Section as the office, pursuant to
17 National Telecommunications and Information Administration of United States
18 Department of Commerce, NTIA, requirements.
19 B.(1) For the projects outlined in Subsection A of this Section, a stop-
20 work order issued solely for alleged marking noncompliance or excavation zone
21 disputes shall not take immediate effect unless the issuing authority makes a
22 written determination that an imminent threat to life or public safety exists.
23 (2) Except as outlined in Paragraph (1) of this Subsection, enforcement
24 of a stop-work order shall be postponed for a four hour review period during
25 which construction may continue. A rapid dispute resolution panel, consisting
26 of representatives of the office, the underground facility operator, the governing
27 authority of the impacted area, and the excavating contractor, shall review
28 relevant documentation and attempt resolution. If no resolution is reached, the
29 office or its designated neutral third party shall issue an independent field
30 determination that is binding for purposes of the stop-work order.
31 C. Nothing in this Section shall be construed to modify federal BEAD
32 Program obligations."
